[The increase in the number of acellular pertussis vaccines given in a lifetime has expanded to one in adolescence and an additional Tdap in adulthood, as well as immunization during the 3rd trimester of pregnancy to assist in protecting infants less than 6 months of age, where much of the morbidity and mortality occurs, and may be straining the production capacity for the pertussis toxoids. - Mod.LL

